me examples on how usefull is to know the ID of each animation.\n\nNote that ice warriors get more bright armor and sword and giants now have chainmail and mace.\nand the ice queen now have white hair, rune b axe, rune shield and white cape \n\n[QUOTE=MARWOLF]Interesting. I''ll have to look more into this. Whenever I tried I ended up with NPCs with huge heads.[/quote:3w02j0a8]\nYea, its very confusing since there are npc definitions both on database and client. For changing stats of the npc it needs to be done at the database but for the name, skin color, size and sprites, those are in the NPCs.rscd file.\n\nLets look at the messed up &quot;Chaos Druid Warrior&quot; ID 555\n\n[img:3w02j0a8]http&#58;//img29&#46;imageshack&#46;us/img29/8020/cdw01&#46;png[/img:3w02j0a8]\n\nLol this guy has 2 sprites for legs! (see blue from the pants?)\n\n[code:3w02j0a8]&lt;NPCDef&gt;\n    &lt;name&gt;Chaos Druid warrior&lt;/name&gt;\n    &lt;description&gt;A crazy evil druid&lt;/description&gt;\n    &lt;command&gt;&lt;/command&gt;\n    &lt;attack&gt;48&lt;/attack&gt;\n    &lt;strength&gt;42&lt;/strength&gt;\n    &lt;hits&gt;40&lt;/hits&gt;\n    &lt;defense&gt;48&lt;/defense&gt;\n    &lt;attackable&gt;true&lt;/attackable&gt;\n    &lt;aggressive&gt;true&lt;/aggressive&gt;\n    &lt;respawnTime&gt;30&lt;/respawnTime&gt;\n    &lt;sprites&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;6&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;2&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;122&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;84&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;42&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n    &lt;/sprites&gt;\n    &lt;hairColour&gt;1&lt;/hairColour&gt;\n    &lt;topColour&gt;65535&lt;/topColour&gt;\n    &lt;bottomColour&gt;255&lt;/bottomColour&gt;\n    &lt;skinColour&gt;15392466&lt;/skinColour&gt;\n    &lt;camera1&gt;145&lt;/camera1&gt;\n    &lt;camera2&gt;220&lt;/camera2&gt;[/code:3w02j0a8]3rd sprite is 2 (normal legs) bottom color is 255 (blue)\nbut in the 8th sprite is 42 (black platelegs) seems like someone forgot to -1 the 3rd sprite.\n122 is staff, and 84 is top wizardrobe red...\n\nLets fix this guy with a black chain and a black mace and red robe bottom\n\n[img:3w02j0a8]http&#58;//img838&#46;imageshack&#46;us/img838/9402/cdw02&#46;png[/img:3w02j0a8]\n\n[code:3w02j0a8]&lt;NPCDef&gt;\n    &lt;name&gt;Chaos Druid warrior&lt;/name&gt;\n    &lt;description&gt;A crazy evil druid&lt;/description&gt;\n    &lt;command&gt;&lt;/command&gt;\n    &lt;attack&gt;48&lt;/attack&gt;\n    &lt;strength&gt;42&lt;/strength&gt;\n    &lt;hits&gt;40&lt;/hits&gt;\n    &lt;defense&gt;48&lt;/defense&gt;\n    &lt;attackable&gt;true&lt;/attackable&gt;\n    &lt;aggressive&gt;true&lt;/aggressive&gt;\n    &lt;respawnTime&gt;30&lt;/respawnTime&gt;\n    &lt;sprites&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;6&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;2&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;121&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;26&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;90&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;-1&lt;/int&gt;\n    &lt;/sprites&gt;\n    &lt;hairColour&gt;1&lt;/hairColour&gt;\n    &lt;topColour&gt;15609904&lt;/topColour&gt;\n    &lt;bottomColour&gt;255&lt;/bottomColour&gt;\n    &lt;skinColour&gt;15392466&lt;/skinColour&gt;\n    &lt;camera1&gt;145&lt;/camera1&gt;\n    &lt;camera2&gt;220&lt;/camera2&gt;\n    &lt;walkModel&gt;6&lt;/walkModel&gt;\n    &lt;combatModel&gt;6&lt;/combatModel&gt;\n    &lt;combatSprite&gt;5&lt;/combatSprite&gt;[/code:3w02j0a8]121 is black mace, 26 black chain, 90 robes bottom and i also changed the top color for the shirt to red (should look more like a warrior now lol).\n\nFor bigger npc just increase camera1 and camera2 numbers.[/quote]', '7141873402a1891cffac8b6e26f7265e', 0, 'iIA=', '3w02j0a8', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0);
