(19, 17, 11, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306028627, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Death view', 'Going to remove the text overlay of &quot;you have died, oh deary me&quot; and instead put a timer so that the player will remain dead and laying there until the timer expires and then teleport them with health returned to respawn coordinates. This will let the player view what happens after they die as sometimes you want to see how things go down after you are killed during PK trips.\n\nThe timer will be a short term solution until a &quot;release&quot; button can be implemented similar to that in WoW.', 'bb37aa61342822f15b2886ee6264cf9e', 0, '', '2retefcu', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(22, 20, 8, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306029034, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Stable 2D Landscape Editor', 'Common Tile Textures:\nIce: 0\nRegular Grass: 70\nBaby Grass: 23\nMedium Grass: 39\nDead Grass: 89\nDust: 111\nSand: 132\nDirt: 146\nMud: (128-158)\nPeat Moss: 168\nDead Ground: 183\nLava Stone: 206\n\nOverlays:\n0: Grass\n1: Road\n2: Water\n3: Wood floor\n4: Bridge\n5: Stone floor\n6: Bank floor\n8: Black hole\n9: Cliff\n11: Lava\n16: Black tile\n\n\n[b:9ouow4e7]2D Landscape Editor Guide:[/b:9ouow4e7]\n\nGo to File &gt; Open\n\nSelect Landscape.wk and click &quot;Open.&quot;\n\nThe landscape is built in sectors - squares that are glued together to form the entire landscape. The game loads the landscape in blocks to reduce lag. Choose a sector or click on a Preset town. You can even click &quot;Jump to coords&quot; to get to a specific spot you know in game.\n\nYou should see a map with colored dots. Those dots can be selected and info can be seen about them on the right side of the window. The XML files that store where and what these dots are - is not a live representation of what is in game. It is 95% accurate - I included the last known XML files before DarkQuest went fully database-driven and moved away from XML files with this Landscape editor build.\n\nWith a tile selected - tiles, that is what each square is called, click &quot;Advanced&quot; &gt; &quot;Toggle Tile Info&quot; - this will let you see additional information about that tile.\n\nElevation is a pain, this is a 2D editor and you cannot judge elevation unless you a.) test it out in a game client, or b.) very every tile on your sector is the right number for elevation.\n\nLuckily, for mass elevation/tile modification, a copy and paste function was built in. You can go to &quot;Edit&quot; &gt; &quot;Copy Tile&quot; and then find your new spot and do &quot;Edit&quot; &gt; &quot;Paste Tile.&quot;\n\nHow can you more quickly copy and paste tiles for large scale creation? First, click on the drop down menu on the right side of the Landscape editor and make sure it says &quot;None.&quot;\n\nNow find the tile you want to copy and click on it.\n\nGo back to the drop down menu on the right side of the Landscape editor and choose &quot;Configure your own.&quot;\n\nBelow, click on the button that reads &quot;Load data.&quot;\n\nThe sliders should now automatically match what the tile info displays. You can now click on other tiles and it will automatically use those settings from the &quot;copied&quot; tile. Be careful not to screw up tiles you already completed though and watch that elevation, its hard to judge.\n\nYou can stop it from automatically using tile data to make new tiles by selecting &quot;None&quot; from that drop down menu.\n\nSo how about moving to a sector adjacent to the one you are currently on. On the right hand side of the Landscape editor, click on the buttons labeled &quot;Up&quot;, &quot;Down&quot;, &quot;Left&quot;, and &quot;Right.&quot; If you have not saved your sector and you click the directional buttons, it will ask you to save it first.\n\nRemember to save often! &quot;File&quot; &gt; &quot;Save Landscape.&quot;\n\nScrew it up? &quot;File&quot; &gt; &quot;Revert Landscape.&quot;\n\n\nSo now its time to test out your landscape. You need to copy this Landscape.wk file into the client cache folder located in your %userprofile\\WK folder. The game server uses the same Landscape.wk file as the client does and both point to the same cache folder in the home directory.', 'cc8f4ce807ae160744058b2aab6eaaa9', 0, 'QA==', '9ouow4e7', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(23, 21, 8, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306029099, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Game Commands', 'Updated 04/07/2011\n\n[i:q1v7ayfp]Note: All commands trickle down. Player Ambassadors, Developermods, and Administrators can do everything Players can. Developermods and Administrators can do everything Players and Player Ambassadors can. Administrators can do everything Players, Player Moderators, and Developermods can.\n[/i:q1v7ayfp]\n\n[b:q1v7ayfp]Admin commands:[/b:q1v7ayfp]\n    unban/ban USERNAME\n    item ID QUANTITY\n    appearance\n    update SECONDS\n    shutdown\n    grounditem ID QUANTITY\n    object ID DIRECTION(1,2,3,4) TRUE/FALSE (save to database?)\n    door ID DIRECTION (1,2,3,4)\n    dropall\n    p2pwild\n    thread\n    noaggro\n    doublexp\n\n\n[b:q1v7ayfp]Developermod commands:[/b:q1v7ayfp]\n    modroom\n    npc ID TRUE/FALSE (store to database?)\n\n\n[b:q1v7ayfp]Player moderator commands:[/b:q1v7ayfp]\n    info PLAYERNAME\n    town TOWNNAME\n\n        {Varrock, Falador, Draynor, Portsarim, Karamja, Alkharid, Lumbridge, Edgeville, Castle, Taverly, Clubhouse, Seers, Barbarian, Rimmington, Catherby, Ardougne, Yanille, Lostcity, Gnome} \n\n    goto PLAYERNAME\n    summon PLAYERNAME\n    invis\n    teleport X Y\n    kick PLAYERNAME\n    take PLAYERNAME\n    put PLAYERNAME\n    nopk\n\n\n[b:q1v7ayfp]Regular user commands:[/b:q1v7ayfp]\n    say TEXT\n    help\n    commands\n    noenergy\n    online\n    onlinelist\n    blink\n    stuck\n    visit', 'b88c3f4f2009d12d722765b58689f54a', 0, 'YA==', 'q1v7ayfp', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(203, 179, 11, 2, 0, '173.245.54.47', 1415322269, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Game Concept', '[b:ez11g4qp]Name:[/b:ez11g4qp] Wolf Kingdom\n[b:ez11g4qp]Color Scheme:[/b:ez11g4qp] Resembling Diablo III\n[b:ez11g4qp]Era:[/b:ez11g4qp] The medieval dark ages\n[b:ez11g4qp]Basis:[/b:ez11g4qp] Rabies has driven the peaceful people of the land to become mad with blood lust.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Goals:[/b:ez11g4qp] Survival as well as the accumulation of wealth and resources.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Factions:[/b:ez11g4qp] Dragon Annihilators, Legionnaires, Rebels. Can attack any members only in the wilderness.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Starting Location:[/b:ez11g4qp] Mystenhaven - final outpost, port town on the edge of the wilderness. Walls have NPC operated cannons to fire at nearby zombies. NPC cannon ammo is unlimited.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Initial Game Engine:[/b:ez11g4qp] Hybrid of Moparscape Classic and DarkQuest\n[b:ez11g4qp]Content:[/b:ez11g4qp] Eventually all original sprites once mechanics and main code are finished\n[b:ez11g4qp]Financing:[/b:ez11g4qp] Owner financed, will not accept donations or use advertisements.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Licencing:[/b:ez11g4qp] Open source and free to play\n[b:ez11g4qp]Release Date:[/b:ez11g4qp] Q1 2015\n[b:ez11g4qp]Player Support:[/b:ez11g4qp] Community provided via forum and IRC channel.\n[b:ez11g4qp]PVP:[/b:ez11g4qp] All wilderness areas surrounding towns will be PVP enabled.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Clans:[/b:ez11g4qp] Support for clans and temporary parties with related chat channels and mini map beacons.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Experience:[/b:ez11g4qp] All players will be the same level. Armor and weaponry will degrade with use. Skills and clan support matter.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Bots:[/b:ez11g4qp] Automated player bots will not survive in the wilderness against human players and zombies, grinding not needed.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Skills:[/b:ez11g4qp] Leather working, smithing, crafting, tanning, hunting, woodcutting, cooking, fishing, herblaw, and beer brewing.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Respawn Frequency:[/b:ez11g4qp] Ground items respawn in the wilderness every 4 hours. Resources respawn every 10 minutes (trees, rocks, fish, NPC animals) Zombies respawn every 5 minutes.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Spawn Locations:[/b:ez11g4qp] Zombies, resources, and ground items spawn in set locations throughout only the wilderness.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Zombies:[/b:ez11g4qp] Set to aggressive, wander distance set to &gt;= 40x40 tiles. Drops: random resources, bones. Set to poisonous.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Player Death:[/b:ez11g4qp] Respawn in Mystenhaven, lose all carried items.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Rabies Infection:[/b:ez11g4qp] If poisoned with rabies while in combat, death is guaranteed. Cannot consume food or potions to heal. All friendly NPCs now set aggressive and attackable. NPC operated fort wall cannons now fire upon. Able to poison/infect other players and friendly NPCs to become zombies.\n[b:ez11g4qp]NPC vs NPC:[/b:ez11g4qp] Zombie NPCs can attack friendly NPCs and infect them to become zombies.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Hunger, Thirst, Health:[/b:ez11g4qp] Thirst and hunger slowly increase over time. Food and drink must be consumed to replenish. 100% hunger or 100% thirst causes health to be lost quickly. Health replenishes automatically over time or with use of healing potions.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Economy:[/b:ez11g4qp] Food, drinks, potions, resources, and crafted supplies can be traded between players at any price. No auction house or general store NPCs. Gold coins can be traded for beer brewing kits and other skill needed tools or between players as currency if they choose.\n[b:ez11g4qp]Game Government:[/b:ez11g4qp] No moderators, no oversight, and no rules. Play any way that works best.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nI want to start players off beside a boat at a dock.The dock is connected to the inside of a walled fort.\n\nOutside of the fort are badlands where players can kill each other.\n\nInside the fort/port is somewhat a new player training area.\n\nNew players can get some training and beginning items but there are also high level player shops.\n\nNew players must venture through the badlands and eventually reach the grassy plains. There they can find a sprawling city.\n\nTrading, merchanting, and ruthless gangs reside in the city. Outside are fields of flax, wheat, and stream for fishing.\n\nThe city and the fort have several NPCs and players must do quests for to gain enough &quot;respect points&quot; to do additional quests. Early quests would require running back and forth to transport items for delivery.\n\nI''ll surround the corners of the landscape that have not been used with trees so players cannot walk further. That already is a ton of content. Once that is all done, more can be developed and thought of.\n\nI want high level players to be able to cast portals that &quot;evaporate&quot; after a minute for point to point transportation by both them and their clan members. I also want players to be able to cast a preventative spell to render enemy players (in badlands) unable to cast teleport spells.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nDesigning the game to support an ultra small online population without feeling empty with only 1-5 online players at a time yet capable of not being broken with 100 online players.\n\nSet ground items to last for 4 hours and discovered maximum ground items in the viewing area before client crashing is 1000, normal players will be hard pressed to reach that limit. I may disable backpack spill over of items onto the ground to guarantee that but it might not be necessary - resources will be well spread apart and not respawn quickly, such as trees.\n\nMade dropped items visible to other players after 5 seconds instead of 1 minute to increase competition.\n\nRodgerwilco suggested shared chests, similar to clan banks. Decided I didn''t want persistent database saving of all the junk put in chests and instead copied the shop code so that individual chest objects can be set up. Will be removing the &quot;shop&quot; sell/buy method and instead have it operate like a bank that other players can interact with. By using the shop code on server reset, only designated items put in by game developers will be always within the chests that will be placed at various places in the wilderness at first, such as torn paper scrolls, candles, a few coins, an iron dagger, leather armor, dried meat, wine casks, etc. Server will automatically reset, perhaps once a day to freshen everything up. I will set it so that items placed in chests will not vanish over time the way they do in shops. Looking to create a new chest window within the client so that it will not resemble the shop window and instead be closer to the bank window. Will add a deposit all items in backpack button on both chest and bank windows.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\nGoing to permit the player skin sprites to be replaced with that of wolves with various fur colors (black, white, grey, and red) on demand.\n\nWhile in wolf form, items cannot be wielded and backpack is disabled with all but one item within dropping to the ground. (One item can be held by the teeth) Stats will have a reasonable bonus, similar to Skyrim werewolves. Wolf form can last until the player chooses to change into a human. Wolf form is not immune to zombie/rabies infection. Infected wolves will become green colored, like infected player zombies and all friendly NPCs will become aggressive. Zombie faction can attack all other factions and the reverse is true. Players in wolf form that have not been infected will remain friendly with the same factions as they are in human form.\n\nI want to increase walking speed for the wolf form but need help figuring out how.\n\nPets cannot follow while the player is in wolf form as the associated capture crystals will not be in the player backpack and they would be naturally too afraid to follow a wolf anyway.\n\nAgility will be a wolf form required skill and can allow a single rare item to be retrieved from otherwise impossible to pass obstacles that only wolves can reach. Various quests will rely on this as learning tutorials for new players.\n\nA story line of quests will be written to tell about the origination of the plague curse upon the Wolf Kingdom.', 'becdc6b43f5899a4153158aa3b3b497c', 0, 'QA==', 'ez11g4qp', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(30, 29, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030449, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Dead trees', '[code:qmnzf5bt]import java&#46;util&#46;ArrayList;[/code:qmnzf5bt]\n\n[code:qmnzf5bt]case 88&#58; // Live trees\n                owner&#46;setBusy(true);\n                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;The tree seems to lash out at you!&quot;);\n                World&#46;getWorld()&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new ShortEvent(owner) {\n                                public void action() {\n                                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;The tree seems to lash out at you!&quot;);\n                                int damage = owner&#46;getCurStat(3) / 5;    \n                                owner&#46;setLastDamage(damage);\n                                owner&#46;setCurStat(3, owner&#46;getCurStat(3) - damage);\n                                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendStat(3);\n                                ArrayList&lt;Player&gt; playersToInform = new ArrayList&lt;Player&gt;();\n                                playersToInform&#46;addAll(owner&#46;getViewArea()&#46;getPlayersInView());\n                                for (Player p &#58; playersToInform)\n                                        p&#46;informOfModifiedHits(owner);\n                                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;You are badly scratched by the tree&quot;);  \n                                owner&#46;setBusy(false);\n                                                }\n                                });\n                                break;[/code:qmnzf5bt]', '3a1e0c3a1344ac9ab41f94d4dda96a85', 0, 'AIA=', 'qmnzf5bt', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(31, 30, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030512, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Sheep Ammy', '<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QsJSexz5l34">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QsJSexz5l34</a><!-- m -->\n\nput this in your itemwieldabledef.xml\nthen equip item 1009\n\n[code:101kl0q9]\n\n        &lt;entry&gt;\n                &lt;int&gt;1009&lt;/int&gt;\n                &lt;ItemWieldableDef&gt;\n                        &lt;sprite&gt;130&lt;/sprite&gt;\n                        &lt;type&gt;1024&lt;/type&gt;\n                        &lt;wieldPos&gt;8&lt;/wieldPos&gt;\n                        &lt;armourPoints&gt;20&lt;/armourPoints&gt;\n                        &lt;weaponAimPoints&gt;0&lt;/weaponAimPoints&gt;\n                        &lt;weaponPowerPoints&gt;0&lt;/weaponPowerPoints&gt;\n                        &lt;magicPoints&gt;0&lt;/magicPoints&gt;\n                        &lt;prayerPoints&gt;0&lt;/prayerPoints&gt;\n                        &lt;rangePoints&gt;0&lt;/rangePoints&gt;\n                        &lt;requiredStats&gt;\n                        &lt;/requiredStats&gt;\n                        &lt;femaleOnly&gt;false&lt;/femaleOnly&gt;\n                &lt;/ItemWieldableDef&gt;\n        &lt;/entry&gt;\n[/code:101kl0q9]', '8cbde9891069c79fa895f6186d6c9740', 0, 'AIA=', '101kl0q9', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(32, 31, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030537, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Change client version in RSCA source', 'The fuckers hid it. The config class for CLIENT_VERSION= is fake.\n\nIt is hidden in the GameWindowMiddleMan class:\n\n[code:1l4q084v]    gameBoxPrint(&quot;Connection lost! Please wait&#46;&#46;&#46;&quot;,\n                        &quot;Attempting to re-establish&quot;);\n            else\n                loginScreenPrint(&quot;Please wait&#46;&#46;&#46;&quot;, &quot;Connecting to server&quot;);\n\n            streamClass = new StreamClass(makeSocket(Config&#46;SERVER_IP, Config&#46;SERVER_PORT), this);\n            streamClass&#46;maxPacketReadCount = maxPacketReadCount;\n            long l = DataOperations&#46;stringLength12ToLong(user);\n            streamClass&#46;createPacket(32);\n            streamClass&#46;addByte((int) (l &gt;&gt; 16 &amp; 31L));\n            // edit KO9\n            streamClass&#46;addString(&quot;ORG&#46;RSCANGEL&#46;CLIENT&#46;MUDCLIENT-W3B5&quot;);\n            // edit\n            streamClass&#46;finalisePacket();\n            long sessionID = streamClass&#46;read8ByteLong();\n            if (sessionID == 0L) {\n                loginScreenPrint(&quot;Login server offline&#46;&quot;,\n                        &quot;Please try again in a few mins&quot;);\n                return;\n            }\n            System&#46;out&#46;print(&quot;Session ID&#58; &quot; + sessionID);\n            int sessionRotationKeys&#91;&#93; = new int&#91;4&#93;;\n            sessionRotationKeys&#91;0&#93; = (int) (Math&#46;random() * 99999999D);\n            sessionRotationKeys&#91;1&#93; = (int) (Math&#46;random() * 99999999D);\n            sessionRotationKeys&#91;2&#93; = (int) (sessionID &gt;&gt; 32);\n            sessionRotationKeys&#91;3&#93; = (int) sessionID;\n            DataEncryption dataEncryption = new DataEncryption(new byte&#91;117&#93;);\n            if (reconnecting)\n                dataEncryption&#46;addByte(1);\n            else\n                dataEncryption&#46;addByte(0);\n            dataEncryption&#46;add4ByteInt(52);\n            dataEncryption&#46;add4ByteInt(sessionRotationKeys&#91;0&#93;);\n            dataEncryption&#46;add4ByteInt(sessionRotationKeys&#91;1&#93;);\n            dataEncryption&#46;add4ByteInt(sessionRotationKeys&#91;2&#93;);\n            dataEncryption&#46;add4ByteInt(sessionRotationKeys&#91;3&#93;);\n            dataEncryption&#46;addString(user);\n            dataEncryption&#46;addString(pass);[/code:1l4q084v]See that?\n[code:1l4q084v]            dataEncryption&#46;add4ByteInt(52);[/code:1l4q084v]Change the 52 to whatever version your server is and it will work.', 'e1d074bfe0c26b1fdab228355bbf5726', 0, 'AIA=', '1l4q084v', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(33, 32, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030559, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Removing empty vials', 'This will basically remove empty vials out of your inventory once you have finished all doses of the potion. In your InvActionHandler class, find:\n\n[code:26q84e8q]\n                owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;remove(item);\n                owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;add(new InvItem(newItem));\n                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendInventory();\n                owner&#46;setBusy(false);\n[/code:26q84e8q]Now the part you want to look at is the ''newItem''. As this is the int used to identify the new item to be added, above that line, you want to add a check to see if the newItem being added is the empty vial.\n\n[code:26q84e8q]\n                if(newItem == 465) { // Empty vial ID\n                    owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;remove(newItem); // Remove the newItem\n                    owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendInventory(); // Send the inventory\n                    owner&#46;setBusy(false); // Make sure you set the player''s busy status\n                } else {\n                    owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;remove(item);\n                    owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;add(new InvItem(newItem));\n                    owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendInventory();\n                    owner&#46;setBusy(false);\n                }\n            }\n[/code:26q84e8q]', '2ab739f204b3ec4d7601f5e3d3bc74a3', 0, 'AIA=', '26q84e8q', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(34, 33, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030582, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Charged dragonstone ammy', 'Here is pretty much a replica of the real RSC Dragonstone Amulet. This has been wrote for my new source that is currently in development.\n\n[code:2u79mk6j]\n                        case 597&#58; // Charged Dragonstone Amulet\n                            player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;You rub the amulet&quot;);\n                            world&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new ShortEvent(player) {\n                                public void action() {\n                                    player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;Where would you like to teleport to?&quot;);\n                                    world&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new MiniEvent(player) {\n                                        public void action() {\n                                            String&#91;&#93; teleportLocations = new String&#91;&#93; { &quot;Edgeville&quot;, &quot;Karamja&quot;, &quot;Draynor village&quot;, &quot;Al Kharid&quot;, &quot;Nowhere&quot; };\n                                            owner&#46;setMenuHandler(new MenuHandler(teleportLocations) {\n                                                public void handleReply(final int option, final String reply) {\n                                                    /**\n                                                     * Check to see if the player is already\n                                                     * busy or the item has a null value\n                                                     */\n                                                    if((owner&#46;isBusy()) || (owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;get(item) == null)) {\n                                                        return;\n                                                    }\n                                                    /**\n                                                     * Check the player''s location to make sure\n                                                     * they aren''t in the modroom or wilderness\n                                                     */\n                                                    if((owner&#46;getLocation()&#46;wildernessLevel() &gt;= 30) || (owner&#46;getLocation()&#46;inModRoom())) {\n                                                        owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;A magical force stops you from teleporting&#46;&quot;);\n                                                        return;\n                                                    }\n                                                    owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendSound(&quot;spellok&quot;);\n                                                    switch(option) {\n                                                        case 0&#58; // Edgeville\n                                                            owner&#46;teleport(226, 447, true);\n                                                            break;\n                                                        case 1&#58; // Karamja\n                                                            owner&#46;teleport(360, 696, true);\n                                                            break;\n                                                        case 2&#58; // Draynor Village\n                                                            owner&#46;teleport(214, 632, true);\n                                                            break;\n                                                        case 3&#58; // Al Kharid\n                                                            owner&#46;teleport(72, 696, true);\n                                                            break;\n                                                        case 4&#58; // Nowhere\n                                                            break;\n                                                        default&#58;\n                                                            return;\n                                                        }\n                                                        if((DataConversions&#46;random(0, 5) == 1) &amp;&amp; (owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;remove(item) &gt; -1)) {\n                                                            owner&#46;getInventory()&#46;add(new InvItem(DRAGONSTONE_AMULET, 1));\n                                                            owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendInventory();\n                                                        }\n                                                    }\n                                                });\n                                                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMenu(teleportLocations);\n                                            }\n                                        });\n                                    }\n                                });\n                                break;\n[/code:2u79mk6j]', '636529b04798e53a71f86c1a5dc3ef2f', 0, 'AIA=', '2u79mk6j', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(35, 34, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306030645, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Cooking', '<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/index.php?topic=339.0">http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/in ... opic=339.0</a><!-- m -->\n\n<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/index.php?topic=338.0">http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/in ... opic=338.0</a><!-- m -->\n\n<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/index.php?topic=336.0">http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/in ... opic=336.0</a><!-- m -->\n\n<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/index.php?topic=337.0">http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/in ... opic=337.0</a><!-- m -->\n\n<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/index.php?topic=335.0">http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/in ... opic=335.0</a><!-- m -->\n\n<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/index.php?topic=332.0">http://www.rscdevelopment.smfnew.com/in ... opic=332.0</a><!-- m -->', 'acdcb0f79d22b0077d3ac27025ad518c', 0, '', '2660r4wh', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
