(90, 89, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306032493, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'xEnt''s F2P boundary loading', 'I have modified this for compatibility with EasyRSC/Noobscape.\n\n\n&quot;I''ll help, just because theres no need to spend time removing all the member objects manually (some code i have of boundary''s that should not load 99% of objects/items/npcs in members land)&quot;\n\nIn Formulae.java, add this to your imports:\n[code:n0e8s977]import org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;server&#46;entityhandling&#46;locs&#46;*;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;server&#46;util&#46;*;[/code:n0e8s977]Then further below, under the public static final entries, insert:\n\n[code:n0e8s977]/**\n         * Cubic P2P boundaries&#46; MinX, MinY - MaxX, MaxY\n         */\n        public static final java&#46;awt&#46;Point&#91;&#93;&#91;&#93; P2P_LOCS = {\n                { new java&#46;awt&#46;Point(436, 432), new java&#46;awt&#46;Point(777, 906) },\n                { new java&#46;awt&#46;Point(48, 96), new java&#46;awt&#46;Point(335, 142) },\n                { new java&#46;awt&#46;Point(343, 567), new java&#46;awt&#46;Point(457, 432) },\n\n        };\n        \n        /**\n         * Performs coordinate checks on the locations in the P2P_LOCS array\n         * to decide whether items/object/npc''s/general x,y coordinates are in P2P area\n         * @param objs - ItemLoc, GameObjectLoc, NPCLoc or an Integer&#46;\n         * @return - true if inside P2P area, otherwise false&#46;\n         */\n        public static boolean isP2P(Object&#46;&#46;&#46; objs) {\n                int x = -1;\n                int y = -1;\n                if(objs&#46;length == 1) {\n                        Object obj = objs&#91;0&#93;;\n                        if(obj instanceof GameObjectLoc) {\n                                x = ((GameObjectLoc)obj)&#46;x;\n                                y = ((GameObjectLoc)obj)&#46;y;\n                        } else if((obj instanceof ItemLoc)) {\n                                x = ((ItemLoc)obj)&#46;x;\n                                y = ((ItemLoc)obj)&#46;y;\n                        } else if(obj instanceof NPCLoc) {\n                                x = ((NPCLoc)obj)&#46;startX;\n                                y = ((NPCLoc)obj)&#46;startY;\n                        }\n                } else {\n                        if(objs&#91;0&#93; instanceof Integer &amp;&amp; objs&#91;1&#93; instanceof Integer) {\n                                x = (Integer)objs&#91;0&#93;;\n                                y = (Integer)objs&#91;1&#93;;\n                        }\n                };\n                if(x == -1)\n                        return false;\n                for(int i=0; i &lt; P2P_LOCS&#46;length; i++) {\n                        for(int ele=0; ele &lt; 4; ele++) {\n                                if(x &gt;= P2P_LOCS&#91;i&#93;&#91;0&#93;&#46;getX() &amp;&amp;  x &lt;= P2P_LOCS&#91;i&#93;&#91;1&#93;&#46;getX()\n                                                &amp;&amp; y &gt;= P2P_LOCS&#91;i&#93;&#91;0&#93;&#46;getY() + ((ele) * 944) &amp;&amp; y &lt;= P2P_LOCS&#91;i&#93;&#91;1&#93;&#46;getY() + ((ele) * 944))\n                                        return true;\n                        }\n                }                \n                return false;\n        }[/code:n0e8s977]\nThen replace this over your old stuff in WorldLoader.java:\n\n[code:n0e8s977]                for(GameObjectLoc gameObject &#58; (List&lt;GameObjectLoc&gt;)PersistenceManager&#46;load(&quot;locs/GameObjectLoc&#46;xml&#46;gz&quot;)) {\n                        if(!Formulae&#46;isP2P(gameObject))\n                                world&#46;registerGameObject(new GameObject(gameObject));\n                }\n                for(ItemLoc item &#58; (List&lt;ItemLoc&gt;)PersistenceManager&#46;load(&quot;locs/ItemLoc&#46;xml&#46;gz&quot;)) {\n                        if(!Formulae&#46;isP2P(item))\n                                world&#46;registerItem(new Item(item));\n                }\n                for(NPCLoc npc &#58; (List&lt;NPCLoc&gt;)PersistenceManager&#46;load(&quot;locs/NpcLoc&#46;xml&#46;gz&quot;)) {\n                        if(!Formulae&#46;isP2P(npc)) {\n                                world&#46;registerNpc(new Npc(npc));\n                        }\n                }[/code:n0e8s977]&quot;Few small P2P locations i have not added to the point array, you can do that your selves.&quot;', '32e54d3009ffc51ed3cb88f866ffb667', 0, 'AIA=', 'n0e8s977', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(91, 90, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306032524, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Tutorial Island progression tracker', 'This will just keep a tracker on the client when you are on the tutorial island.\n\nIn your Mudclient class, add:\n\n[code:28v4jckf]\nprivate int tutorial;\n[/code:28v4jckf]Now find:\n\n[code:28v4jckf]\nif (!notInWilderness) {\n[/code:28v4jckf]Above that, add:\n\n[code:28v4jckf]\n      if (inTutorialIsland()) {\n        int i9 = 110;\n        showInfo = false;\n        gameGraphics&#46;drawString(&quot;@or1@TUTORIAL ISLAND&quot;, 15, i9, 3, 16776960);\n        i9 += 13;\n        gameGraphics&#46;drawString(&quot;@whi@Completion Percentage&quot;, 10, i9, 1, 16776960);\n        i9 += 13;\n        gameGraphics&#46;drawString(&quot;@gre@&quot; + tutorial + &quot;%&quot;, 65, i9, 3, 16776960);\n      }\n[/code:28v4jckf]Now find:\n\n[code:28v4jckf]\npublic boolean isOnFriendsList(String username)\n[/code:28v4jckf]Above that, add:\n\n[code:28v4jckf]\n    public boolean inTutorialIsland() {\n        int x = sectionX + areaX;\n        int y = sectionY + areaY;\n        return (( x &lt;= 248) &amp;&amp; (x &gt;= 188) &amp;&amp; (y &lt;= 769) &amp;&amp; (y &gt;= 725));\n    }\n[/code:28v4jckf]Now find:\n\n[code:28v4jckf]\n            if (command == 126) {\n                fatigue = DataOperations&#46;getUnsigned2Bytes(data, 1);\n                return;\n            }\n[/code:28v4jckf]Below that, add:\n\n[code:28v4jckf]\n            if (command == 133) {\n                tutorial = DataOperations&#46;getUnsigned2Bytes(data, 1);\n                return;\n            }\n[/code:28v4jckf]That is all that is needed client side... Now in your server source, open your Player class, and add:\n\n[code:28v4jckf]\n    /**\n     * Tutorial Island Progression\n     *        @author Yong Min\n     */\n    private int tutorial = 0;\n\n    public void setTutorialStatus(int tutorial) {\n        this&#46;tutorial = tutorial;\n    }\n    \n    public int getTutorialStatus() {\n        return tutorial;\n    }\n[/code:28v4jckf]Now find where it gets the properties of your CFG files/Template and add:\n\n[code:28v4jckf]\nsetTutorialStatus(Integer&#46;parseInt(props&#46;getProperty(&quot;tutorial&quot;)));\n[/code:28v4jckf]And:\n\n[code:28v4jckf]\npr&#46;setProperty(&quot;tutorial&quot;, &quot;&quot; + this&#46;getTutorialStatus());\n[/code:28v4jckf]Now find:\n\n[code:28v4jckf]\nsender&#46;sendFatigue();\n[/code:28v4jckf]And under that, add:\n\n[code:28v4jckf]\nsender&#46;sendTutorialStatus();\n[/code:28v4jckf]Now open your MiscPacketBuilder class, and add:\n\n[code:28v4jckf]\n    /**\n     * Updates the tutorial status percentage\n     */\n    public void sendTutorialStatus() {\n        RSCPacketBuilder s = new RSCPacketBuilder();\n        s&#46;setID(133);\n        s&#46;addShort(player&#46;getTutorialStatus());\n        packets&#46;add(s&#46;toPacket());\n    }\n[/code:28v4jckf]And in your Template in the players DIR, add:\n\n[code:28v4jckf]\ntutorial=0\n[/code:28v4jckf]', 'd66dd813e234a52f8c3daf04f103c5e1', 0, 'AIA=', '28v4jckf', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(92, 91, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306032572, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Clue scrolls and treasure trails', 'We will need to branch into the development of a treasure trails system.\n\nDifficult NPCs will be able to occasionally drop clue scrolls. The scrolls will be level 1, 2, or 3. Higher the level, better the prize. You can accumulate as many scrolls as you want. Each scroll will give a clue and you will have to figure out what it means. Upon arriving at the location, using the clue scroll on an object could trigger the reward. (Item on object)\n\nUpon reward, scroll would be removed from inventory, reward items added to inventory, and a message displayed to the player that they completed the treasure trail. The player would not know what they received from the clue until the reward.\n\nWe will need 20-30 clues created.\n\n[quote=&quot;Yong Min&quot;:13oc15xr]Ok, to start the coding process with this, let''s define what rewards can be received upon completion of the clue scrolls. I''ll use the id [81] for Rune 2-handed Sword for now until we have accumulated all possible reward IDs.\n\n[code:13oc15xr]\npublic final int&#91;&#93; levelOneRewards = { 81 };\n\npublic final int&#91;&#93; levelTwoRewards = { 81 };\n\npublic final int&#91;&#93; levelThreeRewards = { 81 };\n[/code:13oc15xr][EDIT]\nAnd a quick way of randomizing those rewards (may tweak later)..\n\n[code:13oc15xr]\nplayer&#46;setRandomReward(levelOneRewards&#91;(int)(Math&#46;random() * levelOneRewards&#46;length)&#93;);\n\nplayer&#46;setRandomReward(levelTwoRewards&#91;(int)(Math&#46;random() * levelTwoRewards&#46;length)&#93;);\n\nplayer&#46;setRandomReward(levelThreeRewards&#91;(int)(Math&#46;random() * levelThreeRewards&#46;length)&#93;);\n[/code:13oc15xr][code:13oc15xr]\npublic int clueReward = 0;\n\npublic void setRandomReward(int reward) {\n     this&#46;clueReward = reward;\n}\n\npublic int getRandomReward() {\n    return clueReward;\n}\n[/code:13oc15xr][EDIT]\nAnd a quick boolean to check if we are on a clue scroll or not (so only 1 clue can be done at any one time).\n\n[code:13oc15xr]\npublic boolean clueStatus = false; // By default the player has no clue\n\npublic boolean getClueStatus() {\n    return clueStatus;\n}\n\npublic void setClueStatus(boolean clueStatus) {\n    this&#46;clueStatus = clueStatus;\n}\n[/code:13oc15xr][/quote:13oc15xr]', '0e3581335bcd636fd098c04d31701c8d', 0, 'gIA=', '13oc15xr', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0);
