(129, 126, 12, 2, 0, '65.190.15.53', 1306115578, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Database calls', 'Simplified gameserver / loginserver communication.\n\nWhen querying something from the login server you should not have to write a new function that returns specific data to a specific packet. A lot easier would be to write:\n\n[code:2mwmnwv0]World&#46;getWorld()&#46;fromDB(“SELECT * FROM TABLE”);[/code:2mwmnwv0]\n which sends the query to the LS which returns the value from the database right back to you.', 'e6a47b2d953636abc4759c46131c8617', 0, 'AIA=', '2mwmnwv0', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
