(170, 150, 12, 2, 0, '69.134.170.79', 1318297822, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'on-demand client MP3 player', 'I was messing around with the RSCA source (because I was bored), and noticed they had a Mp3 class in the client, so I decided to make use of it.\n\nWhat I did was make it so that you issue a command, and it makes the client play a Mp3.  If they don''t have it, it downloads it into the cache folder, and will load each time the client starts.\n\nServer side:\n\nIn MiscPacketBuilder class add:\n[code:2e501nmt]\n        public void sendMP3(String soundName) {\n                RSCPacketBuilder s = new RSCPacketBuilder();\n                s&#46;setID(22);\n                s&#46;addBytes(soundName&#46;getBytes());\n                packets&#46;add(s&#46;toPacket());\n        }[/code:2e501nmt]\n\nIn the CommandHandler class add:\n[code:2e501nmt]\n        if(cmd&#46;equals(&quot;sound&quot;)) {\n                StringBuilder command = new StringBuilder();\n                for(String s &#58; args)\n                        command&#46;append(s);\n                for (Player p &#58; world&#46;getPlayers())\n                        p&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMP3(new String(command));\n                return;\n        }[/code:2e501nmt]\n\nIn the client:\n\nIn the mudclient class, look for:\n[code:2e501nmt]\nif (command == 22) {[/code:2e501nmt]\n\nInside that statement, make it look like this:\n[code:2e501nmt]\n                                String s = new String(data, 1, length - 1);\n                                Mp3 t;\n                                String name = s&#46;substring(s&#46;lastIndexOf(''/'') + 1);\n                                if (MP3Sounds&#46;containsKey(name)) {\n                                        t = new Mp3(MP3Sounds&#46;get(name)&#46;getPath());\n                                } else {\n                                        File f = downloadFile(s, &quot;&#46;&quot; + File&#46;separator + &quot;rsca&quot; + File&#46;separator + name);\n                                        MP3Sounds&#46;put(name, f);\n                                        t = new Mp3(f&#46;getPath());\n                                }\n                                t&#46;play();\n                                return;[/code:2e501nmt]\n\nAdd this method into the mudclient class:\n[code:2e501nmt]\n        private File downloadFile(String src, String dest) {\n                BufferedInputStream in;\n                try {\n                        in = new BufferedInputStream(new URL(src)&#46;openStream());\n                        File file = new File(dest);\n                        if (!file&#46;exists())\n                                file&#46;createNewFile();\n                        FileOutputStream fos = new FileOutputStream(dest);\n                        BufferedOutputStream bout = new BufferedOutputStream(fos, 1024);\n                        byte data&#91;&#93; = new byte&#91;1024&#93;;\n                        while (in&#46;read(data, 0, 1024) &gt;= 0) {\n                                bout&#46;write(data);\n                        }\n                        bout&#46;close();\n                        in&#46;close();\n                } catch (MalformedURLException e) {\n                        e&#46;printStackTrace();\n                } catch (IOException e) {\n                        e&#46;printStackTrace();\n                }\n                return new File(dest);\n        }[/code:2e501nmt]\n\nRename the ctfsounds hashmap to, &quot;MP3Sounds&quot;.\n\nMake the loadSounds method in the mudclient class look like this:\n[code:2e501nmt]\n        private final void loadSounds() {\n                try {\n                        drawDownloadProgress(&quot;Unpacking Sound effects&quot;, 90, false);\n                        sounds = load(&quot;sounds1&#46;mem&quot;);\n                        audioReader = new AudioReader();\n                        File dir = new File(&quot;&#46;&quot; + File&#46;separator + &quot;rsca&quot;);\n                        String&#91;&#93; chldrn = dir&#46;list();\n\n                        FilenameFilter filter = new FilenameFilter() {\n                                public boolean accept(File dir, String name) {\n                                        return name&#46;endsWith(&quot;&#46;mp3&quot;);\n                                }\n                        };\n                        \n                        chldrn = dir&#46;list(filter);\n                        for (final String s &#58; chldrn) {\n                                new Thread(new Runnable() {\n                                        public void run() {\n                                                MP3Sounds&#46;put(s, mudclient&#46;loadCachedFile(s));\n                                        }\n                                })&#46;start();\n                        }\n                        return;\n                } catch (Throwable throwable) {\n                        System&#46;out&#46;println(&quot;Unable to init sounds&#58;&quot; + throwable);\n                }\n        }[/code:2e501nmt]\n\nAlso, make sure you don''t forget to import the correct packages.\n\nAn example usage would be ::sound <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://google.com/rickroll.mp3">http://google.com/rickroll.mp3</a><!-- m -->\n\nAdditional benefits of this:\nYou can drop mp3s into the cache directory, and the client will load them.\nYou can play mp3s with a simple command.\nYou now have the ability to easily implement  other things that require downloading files from a url.', '571c4b4e77fa2ab3f94beb398bb5b48b', 0, 'AIA=', '2e501nmt', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0);
