(176, 156, 12, 2, 0, '69.134.170.79', 1318299008, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Zombie World Event', 'I was going to hold a week long world event on RSCA.\n\nThe idea pretty much a rip off of WoW''s blood effect plague, only done intentionally.\n\nI was going to place jars of infected blood around edge.\n\n[img:3s5ro8k2]http&#58;//i31&#46;tinypic&#46;com/2rc7pev&#46;png[/img:3s5ro8k2]\n\nOpening the jar would first infect yourself if you''re not infected (the infection turns you into a zombie), but then will infect people in a certain radius to yourself.\n\n[img:3s5ro8k2]http&#58;//i31&#46;tinypic&#46;com/hrdk44&#46;png[/img:3s5ro8k2]\n\n\nThe green jar is an antidote.\n\nI was thinking, zombies would have a delay on their movement updates to make them move slower and then give normal players a ranged skill of sorts to stop the zombies.\n\nJar opening code:\n\n[code:3s5ro8k2]        } else if (item&#46;getDef()&#46;getCommand()&#46;equalsIgnoreCase(&quot;open&quot;)) {\n                        if(item&#46;getID() == INFECTED_BLOOD) {\n                        if(!player&#46;isInfected()) { player&#46;setInfected(); return; }\n                        long lastUsed = System&#46;currentTimeMillis() - player&#46;lastInfected();\n                        long remaining = 5 - lastUsed / 1000;\n                        InvItem INFECTED_BLOOD_I = new InvItem(1322, 1);\n                        if(lastUsed / 1000 &lt;= 5) { player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;You have to wait &quot; + remaining + &quot; seconds before using that again&#46;&quot;); return; }\n                        showBubble(player, INFECTED_BLOOD_I);\n                        player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;Pools of blood spurt our around you&#46;&quot;);\n                        for (Player v &#58; player&#46;infectedBlood()) {\n                                if(v == player) continue;\n                                int bloodChance = DataConversions&#46;random(0,99);\n                                if(bloodChance &gt;= 15) {\n                                        showBubble(v, INFECTED_BLOOD_I);\n                                        v&#46;setInfected();\n                                        player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;You have infected &quot; + v&#46;getUsername() + &quot; &gt;&#58;D &quot;);\n                                }\n                        }\n                        player&#46;setLastInfected();\n                        return;\n                        }[/code:3s5ro8k2]\n\n[code:3s5ro8k2]int bloodChance = DataConversions&#46;random(0,99);\n                                if(bloodChance &gt;= 15) {[/code:3s5ro8k2]\n\n- You will probably want to adjust this.\n\nInfected blood functions and variables for the model/Player class\n\nPlayer.java:\n[code:3s5ro8k2]        /*\n        * Used for the Infected Blood world event\n        */\n\n        public boolean infected = false;\n        public long lastInfected = System&#46;currentTimeMillis();\n\n        /*\n        * Informs the server that the player has just used Infected Blood and activate the cooldown&#46;\n        */\n\n        public void setLastInfected() {\n                lastInfected = System&#46;currentTimeMillis();\n        }\n\n        /*\n        * Returns the last time a player used Infected Blood&#46;\n        */\n\n        public long lastInfected() {\n                return lastInfected;\n        }\n\n        /*\n        * Is this player infected?\n        */\n\n        public boolean isInfected() {\n                return infected;\n        }\n        /*\n        * This method is used for the Infected Blood world event\n        * @author Ollie\n        */\n\n        public void setInfected() {\n                infected = true;\n                getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;You have been afflicted by the plague&#46;&quot;);\n        }\n\n        public List&lt;Player&gt; infectedBlood() {\n                List&lt;Player&gt; playersInView = viewArea&#46;getPlayersInView();\n                List&lt;Player&gt; radiusPlayers = new ArrayList&lt;Player&gt;();\n                for (Player p &#58; playersInView) {\n                        if((p&#46;getX() - getX() &lt;= 2  || p&#46;getX() - getY() &gt;= -2) &amp;&amp; (p&#46;getY() - getY() &lt;= 2  || p&#46;getY() - getY() &gt;= -2) &amp;&amp; !p&#46;isInfected()) {\n                                radiusPlayers&#46;add(p);\n                        }\n                }\n                return radiusPlayers;\n        }[/code:3s5ro8k2]\n\nYou could give prizes to the last remaining survivor, the zombie who infects the most, the human who cures the most (maybe make antidotes work on infected players too?), etc.\n\nAll of the sprites (apart from the zombie, which hasn''t yet been converted into a sprite) are in RSCAngel''s data directory, <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://rscangel.org/rsca.zip">http://rscangel.org/rsca.zip</a><!-- m -->\n\nLet me know if anyone finishes this. I was really looking forward to getting this in-game, wanted to do a world-event type thing for years.\n\n*Credits:\n\nAll graphical work done by Necroth\nAll coding work done by Ollie', 'b0bc7ee6395d413b5f4417d71a3d21ce', 0, 'CIA=', '3s5ro8k2', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(177, 157, 12, 2, 0, '69.134.170.79', 1318299098, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'EasyRSC disable automatic player registration in client', 'PlayerLoader class\n\nFind\n[code:3e6pltxo]File fi = new File(&quot;players/&quot; + user + &quot;&#46;cfg&quot;);\n                                copy(new File(&quot;players/Template&quot;), fi);\n                                GUI&#46;writeValue(user, &quot;pass&quot;, pass);\n                                Logger&#46;print(&quot;Account Created&#58; &quot; + user, 3);\n                                return 1;\n}[/code:3e6pltxo]\n\nReplace with\n[code:3e6pltxo]\nreturn 0;\n}[/code:3e6pltxo]\n\n\nThis will stop people registering via the client.', 'ae9bdf3e23469e39cfe36fef257d9cf8', 0, 'AIA=', '3e6pltxo', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(178, 158, 12, 2, 0, '69.134.170.79', 1318299280, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'RSCD reporting addition', 'Hello,\n\nwell for some strange reason the reporting was removed from rscd.. so\n\nGoto\n\n[code:1msxmtga]org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;server&#46;packethandler&#46;client&#46;ReportHandler[/code:1msxmtga]\n\nRemove the /* */ or replace the class with\n\n[code:1msxmtga]package org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;server&#46;packethandler&#46;client;\n\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;server&#46;packethandler&#46;PacketHandler;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;server&#46;model&#46;*;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;server&#46;net&#46;Packet;\nimport org&#46;apache&#46;mina&#46;common&#46;IoSession;\n\npublic class ReportHandler implements PacketHandler {\n        public static final World world = World&#46;getWorld();\n\n        public void handlePacket(Packet p, IoSession session) throws Exception {\n                Player player = (Player)session&#46;getAttachment();\n                if(!player&#46;canReport()) {\n                        player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;You may only send one abuse report per minute&#46;&quot;);\n                        return;\n                }\n                \n                world&#46;getServer()&#46;getLoginConnector()&#46;getActionSender()&#46;reportUser(player&#46;getUsernameHash(), p&#46;readLong(), p&#46;readByte());\n                \n                player&#46;setLastReport();\n                player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;Your report has been received, thank you&#46;&quot;);\n        }\n        \n}[/code:1msxmtga]\n\nNow go to \n[code:1msxmtga]org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;packethandler&#46;loginserver&#46;ReportHandler[/code:1msxmtga]\nand replace the rscd_reports with rscd_reports2 &lt;-- only reason i am saying this is because the site is using the rscd_reports? for some strange reason and u need to edit the table\n\nnow add this table to your sql\n\n[code:1msxmtga]CREATE TABLE `rscd_reports2` (\n  `from` varchar(255) NOT NULL,\n  `about` varchar(255) NOT NULL,\n  `time` int(10) unsigned NOT NULL,\n  `reason` int(5) unsigned NOT NULL,\n  `x` int(5) unsigned NOT NULL,\n  `y` int(5) unsigned NOT NULL,\n  `status` varchar(255) NOT NULL\n) ENGINE=MyISAM DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;[/code:1msxmtga]\n\nNow go to Conf/server/PacketHandlers.xml\n\nand add the reporting opcode\n\n[code:1msxmtga]                &lt;PacketHandler&gt;\n                        &lt;ids&gt;\n                                &lt;int&gt;7&lt;/int&gt;\n                        &lt;/ids&gt;\n                        &lt;className&gt;org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;server&#46;packethandler&#46;client&#46;ReportHandler&lt;/className&gt;\n                &lt;/PacketHandler&gt;[/code:1msxmtga]', 'a2e4978701c6152a76f38b98d89bccfa', 0, 'AIA=', '1msxmtga', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(179, 159, 12, 2, 0, '69.134.170.79', 1318299512, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Approaching dead tree', '[img:ayu33ae3]http&#58;//img97&#46;imageshack&#46;us/img97/8615/agrotree01&#46;png[/img:ayu33ae3]\n\n[code:ayu33ae3]import java&#46;util&#46;ArrayList;[/code:ayu33ae3]\n\n[code:ayu33ae3]case 88&#58; // Live trees\n                owner&#46;setBusy(true);\n                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;The tree seems to lash out at you!&quot;);\n                World&#46;getWorld()&#46;getDelayedEventHandler()&#46;add(new ShortEvent(owner) {\n                                public void action() {\n                                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;The tree seems to lash out at you!&quot;);\n                                int damage = owner&#46;getCurStat(3) / 5;    \n                                owner&#46;setLastDamage(damage);\n                                owner&#46;setCurStat(3, owner&#46;getCurStat(3) - damage);\n                                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendStat(3);\n                                ArrayList&lt;Player&gt; playersToInform = new ArrayList&lt;Player&gt;();\n                                playersToInform&#46;addAll(owner&#46;getViewArea()&#46;getPlayersInView());\n                                for (Player p &#58; playersToInform)\n                                        p&#46;informOfModifiedHits(owner);\n                                owner&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;You are badly scratched by the tree&quot;);   \n                                owner&#46;setBusy(false);\n                                                }\n                                });\n                                break;[/code:ayu33ae3]', '2e2b49474d1d7fd7ac0398796a917b87', 0, 'CIA=', 'ayu33ae3', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(180, 160, 12, 2, 0, '69.134.170.79', 1318299698, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Player muting', 'Would be better if you used the LoginServer really, but meh.\n\nAlso, WHERE `user`=&quot; + p.getUsernameHash()); - You should wrap WHERE clauses in single or double quotes for MySQL or you will notice performance problems in MySQLd when you have &gt;40,000 records~\n\n\nThis, far less code for it too. Here''s the code if you want to use the LS..\n\nCommandHandler (unless you want to do it client-sided)\n\n[code:1agxx9z3]if (cmd&#46;equals(&quot;mute&quot;) || cmd&#46;equals(&quot;unmute&quot;)) {\n                boolean muted = cmd&#46;equals(&quot;mute&quot;);\n                loginServer&#46;mutePlayer(player, DataConversions&#46;usernameToHash(args&#91;0&#93;), muted);\n                return;\n                }[/code:1agxx9z3]\n\nNow open MiscPacketBuilder in the PacketBuilder folder.\n\n[code:1agxx9z3]public void mutePlayer(final Player mod, final long user, final boolean mute) {\n                LSPacketBuilder s = new LSPacketBuilder();\n                s&#46;setID(mute ? 16 &#58; 17);\n                s&#46;addLong(user);\n                s&#46;setHandler(connector, new PacketHandler() {\n                        public void handlePacket(Packet p, IoSession session) throws Exception {\n                                if(p&#46;readByte() == 1) {\n                                        Logger&#46;mod(mod&#46;getUsername() + &quot; &quot; + (mute ? &quot;muted&quot; &#58; &quot;unmuted&quot;) + &quot; &quot; + DataConversions&#46;hashToUsername(user));\n                                }\n                                mod&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(p&#46;readString());\n                        }\n                });\n                packets&#46;add(s&#46;toPacket());\n        }[/code:1agxx9z3]\n\nNow goto the LS folder, inside PacketHandler/LoginServer. Create a new handler, in this instance MuteHandler.\n\n[code:1agxx9z3]package org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;packethandler&#46;loginserver;\n\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;packethandler&#46;PacketHandler;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;Server;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;model&#46;World;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;net&#46;LSPacket;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;net&#46;Packet;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;util&#46;DataConversions;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;packetbuilder&#46;loginserver&#46;ReplyPacketBuilder;\n\nimport org&#46;apache&#46;mina&#46;common&#46;IoSession;\n\nimport java&#46;sql&#46;ResultSet;\n\npublic class MuteHandler implements PacketHandler {\n        private ReplyPacketBuilder builder = new ReplyPacketBuilder();\n\n        public void handlePacket(Packet p, IoSession session) throws Exception {\n                final long uID = ((LSPacket)p)&#46;getUID();\n                boolean muted = ((LSPacket)p)&#46;getID() == 16;\n                long user = p&#46;readLong();\n                \n                ResultSet result = Server&#46;db&#46;getQuery(&quot;SELECT u&#46;group_id, p&#46;playermod FROM `users` AS u INNER JOIN `rscd_players` AS p ON p&#46;owner=u&#46;id WHERE p&#46;user=&quot; + user);\n                if(!result&#46;next()) {\n                              builder&#46;setSuccess(false);\n                              builder&#46;setReply(&quot;There is not an account by that username&quot;);\n                }\n                else if(muted &amp;&amp; (result&#46;getInt(&quot;group_id&quot;) &lt; 3 || result&#46;getInt(&quot;playermod&quot;) == 1)) {\n                              builder&#46;setSuccess(false);\n                              builder&#46;setReply(&quot;You cannot mute a (p)mod or admin!&quot;);\n                }\n                      else if(Server&#46;db&#46;updateQuery(&quot;UPDATE `rscd_players` SET `group_id`=''&quot; + (muted ? &quot;8&quot; &#58; &quot;0&quot;) + &quot;'', `muted`=''&quot; + (muted ? &quot;1&quot; &#58; &quot;0&quot;) + &quot;'' WHERE `user` LIKE ''&quot; + user + &quot;''&quot;) == 0) {\n                              builder&#46;setSuccess(false);\n                              builder&#46;setReply(&quot;There is not an account by that username&quot;);\n                      }\n                      else {\n                              World w = Server&#46;getServer()&#46;findWorld(user);\n                              if(w != null) {\n                                      w&#46;getActionSender()&#46;logoutUser(user);\n                              }\n                              builder&#46;setSuccess(true);\n                              builder&#46;setReply(DataConversions&#46;hashToUsername(user) + &quot; has been &quot; + (muted ? &quot;muted&quot; &#58; &quot;unmuted&quot;));\n                      }\n                      builder&#46;setUID(uID);\n                      \n                      LSPacket temp = builder&#46;getPacket();\n                      if(temp != null) {\n                              session&#46;write(temp);\n                      }\n                      \n        }\n        \n}[/code:1agxx9z3]\n\nThen add the packets accordingly to the LSPacketHandlers.xml (16/17) in this case. In case you don''t know what I''m talking about...\n\n[code:1agxx9z3]&lt;PacketHandler&gt;\n                        &lt;ids&gt;\n                                &lt;int&gt;16&lt;/int&gt;\n                                &lt;int&gt;17&lt;/int&gt;\n                        &lt;/ids&gt;\n                        &lt;className&gt;org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;packethandler&#46;loginserver&#46;MuteHandler&lt;/className&gt;\n                &lt;/PacketHandler&gt;[/code:1agxx9z3]\n\nNow for the actual mute, you can approach this a couple different ways, but since I never really took the time to focus on it, I decided to use an if statement in the player model when a mob has sent chat to the chat queue. Be sure to declare the muted group otherwise it won''t work.\n\n[code:1agxx9z3]public boolean isMuted() {\n                return groupID == 8;\n        }[/code:1agxx9z3]\n\n[code:1agxx9z3]public void addMessageToChatQueue(byte&#91;&#93; messageData) {\n                if(isMuted()) {\n                getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;You have been muted&#46; Please contact an administrator for details&quot;);\n                return;\n                }[/code:1agxx9z3]\n\nNOT the best way to do it, but it''s quick if you just want to stop chat from them.', '20e1d3e8dfa17c28b384e57075ec1578', 0, 'AIA=', '1agxx9z3', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(181, 161, 12, 2, 0, '69.134.170.79', 1318299852, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'RSCD Clan Core', 'I''ve noticed a lot of people use an older copypasta version of xEnt''s Party System as their clan system, and thought I would share some insight on how this should be approached. \n\nYou can approach this a numerous amount of ways, but for this to work properly you will need to understand simple packet creation.\n\nYou will need a basic rscdv25 (NOT EASYRSC) and a clean database.\n\nWhat will you get from this? A very basic clan system core, meaning nothing more than understanding communication between the server and database and how you can achieve this without the use of PHP. This will show you HOW TO CREATE A BASIC CLAN via command. You can also achieve this via the client by sending a string(s) back to the server through a packet if you''d like, although I will make a tutorial later for this.\n\nGo to your database (ex: PhpMyAdmin). First you will need to add a new table inside your database, for this I will call it &quot;RSCD_CLANS&quot;. Add 2 fields (you can add more if you want to go detailed), one will be ''owner'' and other will be the ''name''. You will use the varchar type (length usually 255), and leave the default as 0. OWNER will be the player that created it (to prevent double creation), and NAME is self explanatory.\n\nOnce that''s finished, we will add the server-side code to create it. For these next steps, you will need to plug them all in before you compile.\n\nFirst you will open up the CommandHandler inside the PACKET HANDLER. Now here''s the code.\n\n[code:2z9e9fgi]if(cmd&#46;equals(&quot;createclan&quot;)) {\n                long player2 = DataConversions&#46;usernameToHash(player&#46;getUsername());\n                long newStr = DataConversions&#46;usernameToHash(args&#91;0&#93;);\n                loginServer&#46;createClan(player2, newStr);\n                player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;@cya@&#91;@whi@Server@cya@&#93;@whi@&#58; Your clan (@gre@&quot; + DataConversions&#46;hashToUsername(newStr) + &quot;@whi@) has been created&#46;&quot;);\n                return;\n                }[/code:2z9e9fgi]\nWhat does this code do? You will notice this will simply save the string (clan name) into a hash form and sent back to the login server for packet creation. (Ex: ::createclan clanname). Once that is done, the server will send back the hash as a string and send you your name clan name. Simple as that.\n\nNext, time to add a new packet that we will use for the above command. Lets head over the PACKET BUILDER, go to loginserver, then find MiscPacketBuilder. Here is the code we will add.\n\n[code:2z9e9fgi]public void createClan(long player, long clanName) { //Simple Clan Creation\n                LSPacketBuilder s = new LSPacketBuilder();\n                s&#46;setID(18);\n                s&#46;addLong(player);\n                s&#46;addLong(clanName);\n                packets&#46;add(s&#46;toPacket());\n        }[/code:2z9e9fgi]\nWhat does this code do? We created a new void to declare the createClan method we used in the command handler. You will notice that this specific packet will be identified as #18. Packet will grab the data that was sent from the command and form it. Now to finish the packet so we can save the data to the database.\n\nLets now create a new handler, perhaps clan handler. Jump over into the LS folder, go into the packet handler, login server and create a new java file. You can name this whatever.java, but in this example it will be clanHandler.java. Once that''s done, lets enter some code in.\n\n[code:2z9e9fgi]package org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;packethandler&#46;loginserver;\n\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;packethandler&#46;PacketHandler;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;Server;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;net&#46;LSPacket;\nimport org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;net&#46;Packet;\n\nimport org&#46;apache&#46;mina&#46;common&#46;IoSession;\n\nimport java&#46;sql&#46;SQLException;\n\npublic class ClanHandler implements PacketHandler {\n\n        public void handlePacket(Packet p, IoSession session) throws Exception {\n        long user = p&#46;readLong();\n        long clanName = p&#46;readLong();\n                try { Server&#46;db&#46;updateQuery(&quot;INSERT INTO `rscd_clans`(`user`, `name`) VALUES(''&quot; + user + &quot;'', ''&quot; + clanName + &quot;'')&quot;); } catch(SQLException e) { }\n        }\n        \n}[/code:2z9e9fgi]\n\nWhat does this code do? We grabbed the data formed from the packet we created in the last two steps, and now inserting it into the database using a simple query. Simple as that, now it''s time to add the packet to the list.\n\nGo into your server CONF folder, go into the LS folder, then open LSpackethandlers.xml. We will add the new packet that server will recognize as our clan creator. For this example, i''m using the classname ClanHandler as that how the file was saved in the LS packet handler folder. \n\n[code:2z9e9fgi]&lt;PacketHandler&gt;\n                        &lt;ids&gt;\n                                &lt;int&gt;18&lt;/int&gt;\n                        &lt;/ids&gt;\n                        &lt;className&gt;org&#46;rscdaemon&#46;ls&#46;packethandler&#46;loginserver&#46;ClanHandler&lt;/className&gt;\n                &lt;/PacketHandler&gt;[/code:2z9e9fgi]\n\nOnce this is set, save all these files and compile. Go ahead and start your server and try out the command. If you were successful, now you can add more functions and complete your core. This is very basic. If you encounter any problems, feel free to post here and ask questions. I will add more tutorials depending on the feedback, enjoy.', 'f2b5dafcc191f91a0f375a1bab41e8b7', 0, 'AIA=', '2z9e9fgi', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(182, 161, 12, 2, 0, '69.134.170.79', 1318300267, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Re: RSCD Clan Core', 'As for clan name beside your name:\n\nTake a look for:\n\n[code:129ov96l]displayMessage(ourPlayer&#46;name + &quot;&#58; &quot; + s, 2, ourPlayer&#46;admin);[/code:129ov96l]\n\nAnd:\n\n[code:129ov96l]else if (mobUpdateType == 1) { // Player talking[/code:129ov96l]\n\nAnd:\n\n[code:129ov96l]} else if (mobUpdateType == 5) { // Apperance update[/code:129ov96l]\n\nYou will be wanting to use:\n\n\nourPlayer.clan\nmob.clan\n\nAnd also in your Mob class, add:\n\n[code:129ov96l]public String clan;[/code:129ov96l]\n\n*** The contents of this post are for EasyRSC but can be made to work with the code in the thread.', 'ca63b20b9fb817abf0a32bb56cb2ec7d', 0, 'AIA=', '129ov96l', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(184, 163, 12, 2, 0, '69.134.170.79', 1318553016, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Ranks in private messages', 'Hello, this is a tutorial showing you how to implement ranks into your RuneScape Classic client.\n\nLike this:\n[img:ap71zuel]http&#58;//i51&#46;tinypic&#46;com/6nunmw&#46;png[/img:ap71zuel]\n\nFirst of all, we will be holding the names of people who need to be ranked (ex: subscribers and staff) inside a HashMap. There are a couple ways of storing who needs to be in the hashmap, you could send everyone''s names, along with their ranks from the server to the client, or just store them in the client itself (this is what we''ll be doing). Secondly, we''ll need to edit how the private messages are displayed, and to check whether or not the sender/receiver is in the hashmap. Now that we''ve gone through what needs to be done, let''s get down to it.  \n\n1) Add the import for our hashmap in the mudclient,\n[code:ap71zuel]import java&#46;util&#46;HashMap;[/code:ap71zuel]\n\n\n2) Now we must add our hashmap object, as well as our method for checking the hashmap,\n[code:ap71zuel]private HashMap&lt;String, Integer&gt; staffList;\n\npublic final String getRank(String key) {\n        Integer value = staffList&#46;get(key&#46;toLowerCase());\n        if(value == null)\n            return key;\n        else if(value == 4)\n            return &quot;#adm#&quot; + key;\n        else if(value == 3)\n            return &quot;#mod#&quot; + key;\n        else if(value == 2)\n            return &quot;#pmd#&quot; + key;\n        return key;\n    }[/code:ap71zuel]\n\n\n3) In the mudclient''s constructor, initialize the hashmap and add users to it with this,\n[code:ap71zuel]staffList = new HashMap&lt;String, Integer&gt;();\nstaffList&#46;put(&quot;hikilaka&quot;, 4);[/code:ap71zuel]\n\n\n4) Now that the client knows who needs to be ranked, lets display them, search for\n[code:ap71zuel]gameGraphics&#46;drawText(&quot;Enter message to send to &quot; + DataOperations&#46;longToString(privateMessageTarget), 256+xAddition, i, 4, 0xffffff);[/code:ap71zuel]\nand replace it with\n[code:ap71zuel]gameGraphics&#46;drawText(&quot;Enter message to send to &quot; + getRank(DataOperations&#46;longToString(privateMessageTarget)), 256+xAddition, i, 4, 0xffffff);[/code:ap71zuel]\nAlso, a little further down, you should see\n[code:ap71zuel]handleServerMessage(&quot;@pri@You tell &quot; + DataOperations&#46;longToString(privateMessageTarget) + &quot;@cya@&#58; &quot; + s1);[/code:ap71zuel]\nchange that to\n[code:ap71zuel]handleServerMessage(&quot;@pri@You tell &quot; + getRank(DataOperations&#46;longToString(privateMessageTarget)) + &quot;@cya@&#58; &quot; + s1);[/code:ap71zuel]\n\n\n5) Open up the GameWindowMiddleMan class, and add this,\n[code:ap71zuel]protected abstract String getRank(String key);[/code:ap71zuel]\nAlso find these two lines\n[code:ap71zuel]if (friendsListOnlineStatus&#91;i2&#93; == 0 &amp;&amp; status != 0)\n                            handleServerMessage(&quot;@pri@&quot; + DataOperations&#46;longToString(friend) + &quot;@cya@ has logged in&quot;);\n                        if (friendsListOnlineStatus&#91;i2&#93; != 0 &amp;&amp; status == 0)\n                            handleServerMessage(&quot;@pri@&quot; + DataOperations&#46;longToString(friend) + &quot;@cya@ has logged out&quot;);[/code:ap71zuel]\nAnd change them to\n[code:ap71zuel]if (friendsListOnlineStatus&#91;i2&#93; == 0 &amp;&amp; status != 0)\n                            handleServerMessage(&quot;@pri@&quot; + getRank(DataOperations&#46;longToString(friend)) + &quot;@cya@ has logged in&quot;);\n                        if (friendsListOnlineStatus&#91;i2&#93; != 0 &amp;&amp; status == 0)\n                            handleServerMessage(&quot;@pri@&quot; + getRank(DataOperations&#46;longToString(friend)) + &quot;@cya@ has logged out&quot;);[/code:ap71zuel]\n\n\n6) Still in the GameWindowMiddleMan class, search for\n[code:ap71zuel]handleServerMessage(&quot;@pri@&quot; + DataOperations&#46;longToString(user) + &quot;@cya@ tells you&#58; &quot; + msg);[/code:ap71zuel]\nand change that to\n[code:ap71zuel]handleServerMessage(&quot;@pri@&quot; + getRank(DataOperations&#46;longToString(user)) + &quot;@cya@ tells you&#58; &quot; + msg);[/code:ap71zuel]\n\n\n7) You''re done! Finally, ikr? Just compile, run and everything should work fine. If you have any additional questions, feel free to post, or PM me.', '349df5fa9295f5124e8bec71575d32d1', 0, 'CIA=', 'ap71zuel', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(185, 164, 12, 2, 0, '69.134.170.79', 1318553155, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Add mouse wheel listeners to the client', 'Replace Inputs.java with:\n\n[code:1nt44atb]package net&#46;aftermath&#46;client;\n\nimport java&#46;awt&#46;event&#46;KeyEvent;\nimport java&#46;awt&#46;event&#46;KeyListener;\nimport java&#46;awt&#46;event&#46;MouseEvent;\nimport java&#46;awt&#46;event&#46;MouseListener;\nimport java&#46;awt&#46;event&#46;MouseMotionListener;\nimport java&#46;awt&#46;event&#46;MouseWheelEvent;\nimport java&#46;awt&#46;event&#46;MouseWheelListener;\n\npublic class Inputs implements MouseListener, MouseMotionListener, KeyListener, MouseWheelListener {\n    \n    public static KeyListener kl = null;\n    \n    private boolean translate = true;\n    \n    private GameWindow aGameWindow = null;\n    \n    public Inputs(GameWindow gw, boolean trans) {\n        this&#46;aGameWindow = gw;\n        this&#46;translate = trans;\n    }\n    \n    public void keyPressed(KeyEvent e) {\n        aGameWindow&#46;keyDown(e&#46;isControlDown(), e&#46;getKeyCode(), e&#46;getKeyChar());\n        if(kl != null)\n            kl&#46;keyPressed(e);\n    }\n    \n    public void keyReleased(KeyEvent e) {\n        aGameWindow&#46;keyUp(e&#46;isControlDown(), e&#46;getKeyCode(), e&#46;getKeyChar());\n    }\n    \n    public void keyTyped(KeyEvent e) {\n    }\n    \n    public void mouseMoved(MouseEvent e) {\n        aGameWindow&#46;mouseMove(e&#46;getX(), e&#46;getY() - (translate ? 24 &#58; 0));    \n    }\n    \n    public void mouseDragged(MouseEvent e) {\n        aGameWindow&#46;mouseDrag(e&#46;isMetaDown(), e&#46;getX(), e&#46;getY() - (translate ? 24 &#58; 0));\n    }\n    \n    public void mouseExited(MouseEvent e) {\n        mouseMoved(e);\n    }\n    \n    public void mouseEntered(MouseEvent e) {\n        mouseMoved(e);    \n    }\n    \n    public void mousePressed(MouseEvent e) {\n        aGameWindow&#46;mouseDown(e&#46;isMetaDown(), e&#46;getX(), e&#46;getY() - (translate ? 24 &#58; 0));\n    }\n    \n    public void mouseReleased(MouseEvent e) {\n        aGameWindow&#46;mouseUp(e&#46;getX(), e&#46;getY() - (translate ? 24 &#58; 0));\n    }\n    \n    public void mouseClicked(MouseEvent e) {\n    }\n\n    public void mouseWheelMoved(MouseWheelEvent e) {\n        aGameWindow&#46;mouseWheel(e&#46;getWheelRotation());\n    }\n    \n}[/code:1nt44atb]\n\nNow in the GameWindow class add this empty method in:\n[code:1nt44atb]public void mouseWheel(int direction) {}[/code:1nt44atb]\n\nIn the mudclient class, add this method:\n[code:1nt44atb]    public void mouseWheel(int direction) {\n        if (direction &gt; 1)\n            direction += direction;\n        else if (direction &lt; -1)\n            direction -= -direction;\n        if (mouseOverMenu == 4)\n            spellMenu&#46;move_menu_scroll(spellMenuHandle, direction);\n        else if (mouseOverMenu == 5)\n            friendsMenu&#46;move_menu_scroll(friendsMenuHandle, direction);\n        else if (mouseOverMenu == 3)\n            questMenu&#46;move_menu_scroll(questMenuHandle, direction);\n        else if (messagesTab == 1)\n            gameMenu&#46;move_menu_scroll(messagesHandleType2, direction);\n        else if (messagesTab == 2)\n            gameMenu&#46;move_menu_scroll(questHandle, direction);\n        else if (messagesTab == 3)\n            gameMenu&#46;move_menu_scroll(privateHandle, direction);\n    }\n[/code:1nt44atb]\nand finally in the Menu class add this:\n[code:1nt44atb]    public void move_menu_scroll(int menu_handler, int dir) {\n        int x = menu_list_txt_count&#91;menu_handler&#93; - menu_height&#91;menu_handler&#93; / game_image&#46;messageFontHeight_(menu_txt_type&#91;menu_handler&#93;);\n        int y = Math&#46;abs(x - menu_indx&#91;menu_handler&#93;);\n        if (dir &gt; 0) {\n            if (y &lt; dir)\n                menu_indx&#91;menu_handler&#93; += y;\n            else\n                menu_indx&#91;menu_handler&#93; += dir;\n        } else if ((dir &lt; 0) &amp;&amp; (menu_indx&#91;menu_handler&#93; &gt; 0))\n            if (menu_indx&#91;menu_handler&#93; &lt; -dir)\n                menu_indx&#91;menu_handler&#93; -= menu_indx&#91;menu_handler&#93;;\n            else\n                menu_indx&#91;menu_handler&#93; += dir;\n    }[/code:1nt44atb]', 'd09ccac01d662b17c2bca7b9e6bda381', 0, 'AIA=', '1nt44atb', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(186, 165, 12, 2, 0, '69.134.170.79', 1318553372, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Adding exhausting % to mining rocks', 'What this do?\nWill make mining rocks have a random chance to give more ores before it gets exhausted.\nIts fun since you never know how much ore you can obtain from a single rock.\nIt works in similar way &quot;fell&quot; % does for trees\n\nSo lets find Objectaction.java in RSCDv25 or Mining.java on Darkquest. Lets open it and search for &quot;gem&quot;, below the &quot;You found a gem&quot; you will see this:\n[code:1s751o4p]world&#46;registerGameObject(new GameObject(object&#46;getLocation(), 98, object&#46;getDirection(), object&#46;getType()));\nworld&#46;delayedSpawnObject(object&#46;getLoc(), def&#46;getRespawnTime() * 1000);[/code:1s751o4p]\n\nreplace with this:\n[code:1s751o4p]if (DataConversions&#46;random(1, 100) &lt;= def&#46;getExhausted()) {\nworld&#46;registerGameObject(new GameObject(object&#46;getLocation(), 98, object&#46;getDirection(), object&#46;getType()));\nworld&#46;delayedSpawnObject(newobject&#46;getLoc(), def&#46;getRespawnTime() * 1000);\n}[/code:1s751o4p]\n\nNow on ObjectMiningDef.java u need to add\n\n[code:1s751o4p]public int exhausted;[/code:1s751o4p]\nand \nCode:\n[code:1s751o4p]public int getExhausted() {\n    return exhausted;\n    }[/code:1s751o4p]\n\nAnd finally! edit the ObjectMining.xml (located on Server/conf/server/defs/extras) adding the percent value for each mining rock. Like i did with these:\n[code:1s751o4p]&lt;entry&gt;\n&lt;int&gt;176&lt;/int&gt;&lt;!-- Bluerite --&gt;\n&lt;ObjectMiningDef&gt;\n&lt;requiredLvl&gt;1&lt;/requiredLvl&gt;\n&lt;oreId&gt;266&lt;/oreId&gt;\n&lt;exp&gt;5&lt;/exp&gt;\n&lt;respawnTime&gt;15&lt;/respawnTime&gt;\n&lt;exhausted&gt;100&lt;/exhausted&gt;\n&lt;/ObjectMiningDef&gt;\n&lt;/entry&gt;\n&lt;entry&gt;\n&lt;int&gt;100&lt;/int&gt;&lt;!-- Copper --&gt;\n&lt;ObjectMiningDef&gt;\n&lt;requiredLvl&gt;1&lt;/requiredLvl&gt;\n&lt;oreId&gt;150&lt;/oreId&gt;\n&lt;exp&gt;18&lt;/exp&gt;\n&lt;respawnTime&gt;3&lt;/respawnTime&gt;\n&lt;exhausted&gt;20&lt;/exhausted&gt;\n&lt;/ObjectMiningDef&gt;\n&lt;/entry&gt;[/code:1s751o4p]\n\nFor example: a value of 100 means rock will exhaust on one successful swing but a value of 95 means 5% chance of extra ore. \n\nI tested with different values until i fell it was right, this are my exhausting values for each one:\n\nbluerite 100, clay 10, tin 20, cooper 20, iron 40, silver 50, \ncoal 55, gold 60, mith 60, addy 75, rune 95', '1326123226dd1f14c6707de8fd1b6840', 0, 'AIA=', '1s751o4p', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(187, 166, 12, 2, 0, '69.134.170.79', 1318553467, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'WoW-like experience rate', 'What this do:\nWith this low lvl mobs will give small exp and the higher lvl is a mob, the better exp it will give.\n\nThe problem with rscd current formula is that you get rewarded for fighting chickens and rats instead of being rewarded when you fight high lvl npc. Also is more fun training at the strongest enemy that oneself can handle. \n[code:3lcqpfvk]public static int combatExperience(Mob mob) { \n    double exp = (Math&#46;pow(mob&#46;getCombatLevel(), 2) * 0&#46;7) + 20D; \n    return (int) (mob instanceof Player ? (exp / 4D) &#58; exp); \n    }[/code:3lcqpfvk]\n\nNote: This goes in formulae.java and need to replace the old formula. \nNote2: If using an overall exp rate higher than x1 then you should divide .7 and 20 by the number of the new xp rate.\nFor Ex. an exp rate of x10 then it should be like this (Math.pow(mob.getCombatLevel(), 2) * 0.07) + 2D;\n\n\n\nSteve Wrote:  \nThe cb formula really hurts pures though lol.\nIn fact they’re receiving similar xp they would get for a chicken lvl 3, but even better xp for a rat lvl 13. Look at this:\n-------[cb lvl]---[old xp]---[new xp]\nchiken - [3]------[26]------[24.5]\n\nG. Rat - [13]-----[46]------[104.5]\n\nNote that the giant rat being 10 combat lvls higher than the chicken, had less xp than fighting 2 chickens (26 x 2 = 52). But on the new formula fighting that rat gives gives the xp of fighting 4 chickens (26x4 = 104) so even pures are gaining more xp since rats are an easy foe (and u know many train their pures on scorpions or even pirates and that is much better xp with this new formula).\n\nAnd that’s what i want they keep moving-on on better training places leaving the chickens for the new comers (back at rsc chickens,goblins and man were all the time botted, leaving new players without a place to train).', '61fea586810564a48187968e3112e061', 0, 'AIA=', '3lcqpfvk', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(188, 167, 12, 2, 0, '69.134.170.79', 1318553713, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'View all players logged in from a single IP', 'Use this command:\n\n        [code:2iwcyfzg]if(cmd&#46;equalsIgnoreCase(&quot;showchars&quot;)) {\n            Player p = World&#46;getWorld()&#46;getPlayer(DataConversions&#46;usernameToHash(args&#91;1&#93;));\n            if(p == null) {\n                player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;Invalid player name, please retry&#46;&quot;);\n                return;\n            }\n            String out = &quot;&quot;;\n            for(Player _p &#58; World&#46;getWorld()&#46;getPlayers())\n                if(_p&#46;getCurrentIP()&#46;equalsIgnoreCase(p&#46;getCurrentIP()) &amp;&amp; !_p&#46;getUsername()&#46;equalsIgnoreCase(p&#46;getUsername()))\n                    out += &quot;@gre@&quot; + _p&#46;getUsername() + &quot; %&quot;;\n            if(!out&#46;equals(&quot;&quot;))\n                player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendAlert(&quot;Accounts logged in with the same IP as @red@&quot; + p&#46;getUsername() + &quot;&#58; % % &quot; + out, true);\n            else\n                player&#46;getActionSender()&#46;sendMessage(&quot;There are no other accounts logged in with the same IP as @red@&quot; + p&#46;getUsername());\n            return;\n        }[/code:2iwcyfzg]', '3a9f508a99cea40669ef535e8cae4ed0', 0, 'AIA=', '2iwcyfzg', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(201, 177, 8, 2, 0, '173.245.54.47', 1415322004, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Github Project Access', '<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://github.com/Marwolf/Wolf-Kingdom">https://github.com/Marwolf/Wolf-Kingdom</a><!-- m -->\n\n[code:23rnq4n2]git clone https&#58;//github&#46;com/Marwolf/Wolf-Kingdom&#46;git[/code:23rnq4n2]', '2189774b29693764ef9fd6d8f28e51b6', 0, 'AIA=', '23rnq4n2', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(202, 178, 8, 2, 0, '173.245.54.47', 1415322183, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Wolf Kingdom Developer''s Getting Started Guide', '[b:f7j27x0c]Development Software Required:[/b:f7j27x0c]\nNetBeans IDE\nJDK &gt;= 1.7\nANT\nMySQL / MariaDB\nApache2 / Nginx / IIS\n\n[b:f7j27x0c]MySQL Database:[/b:f7j27x0c]\nThe MySQL &quot;lupus_regnum.sql&quot; database import is located inside Wolf-Kingdom-Server.\nUser: &quot;root&quot;\nPassword: &quot;password&quot;\nHost: &quot;localhost&quot;\n\n[b:f7j27x0c]JDK:[/b:f7j27x0c]\nProject compile targets are set for JDK 1.7', '857d597e25d8ce158f02b4aad87becf1', 0, 'QA==', 'f7j27x0c', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(192, 171, 12, 2, 0, '198.86.248.33', 1380836537, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Grounditem fix', 'This is the fix for common bug in rscd, altough, I assume that the problem is in serverside, while I did the temporary fix clientside.\n\nAlso it could be that reines messed up with the client, I just assume its serverside.\n\nSearch for\n[code:19z1l6jw]\nfor (int j3 = 0; j3 &lt; groundItemCount; j3++) {\n[/code:19z1l6jw]\n\nReplace the loop with this:\n[code:19z1l6jw]\n        for (int j3 = 0; j3 &lt; groundItemCount; j3++) {\n                if(!withinRange(groundItemX&#91;j3&#93;, groundItemY&#91;j3&#93;)) {\n                        groundItemType&#91;j3&#93; = -1;\n                        groundItemObjectVar&#91;j3&#93; = -1;\n                        groundItemX&#91;j3&#93; = -1;\n                        groundItemY&#91;j3&#93; = -1;\n                }\n                groundItemX&#91;j3&#93; -= k1;\n                groundItemY&#91;j3&#93; -= l1;\n        }\n[/code:19z1l6jw]\n\nAdd this method somewhere:\n[code:19z1l6jw]\n        public boolean withinRange(int x, int y) {\n                int xDiff = (sectionX + areaX)- x; \n                int yDiff = (sectionY + areaY) - y;\n                return xDiff &lt;= 16 &amp;&amp; xDiff &gt;= -15 &amp;&amp; yDiff &lt;= 16 &amp;&amp; yDiff &gt;= -15;\n        }\n[/code:19z1l6jw]\nWhat this will do is to remove the grounditems that aren''t in range/visible.', '8ee9ea09b69931d71c024aa4a4c371e3', 0, 'AIA=', '19z1l6jw', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(193, 172, 5, 2, 0, '65.190.77.34', 1380853388, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Mass NPCs', 'I remember certain areas in RSC as being absolutely crowded with players. I often had my chat to private only because the local chat was so full of spam from buyers and sellers. Last night, I used the mass NPC command to spawn a ton of random NPCs in a 20x20 area. I suddenly had that old sense of a busy game server again. As long as the amount of NPCs remains under 200, it seems stable. Preferably under 100 is best so real players don''t push the game client beyond it''s limit which would cause it to crash. The server can handle it, just not the client. Could hand pick NPCs that are friendly for public areas, such as towns. Maybe even give them quest-like dialogs that occur every so often randomly..\n\n[img:3dqfqwgj]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/IQxOTcY&#46;png[/img:3dqfqwgj]\n[img:3dqfqwgj]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/OO6Urwx&#46;png[/img:3dqfqwgj]\n[img:3dqfqwgj]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/0yxtV3w&#46;png[/img:3dqfqwgj]\n[img:3dqfqwgj]http&#58;//i&#46;imgur&#46;com/kex1PLD&#46;png[/img:3dqfqwgj]', '753f08877d22079bd60a01c499993890', 0, 'CA==', '3dqfqwgj', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(195, 174, 12, 2, 0, '173.245.52.197', 1381589847, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Mining exhaustion', 'What this do?\n\nWill make mining rocks have a random chance to give more ores before it gets exhausted.\nIts fun since you never know how much ore you can obtain from a single rock.\n\nSo lets find Objectaction.java in RSCDv25 or Mining.java on Darkquest. Lets open it and search for &quot;gem&quot;, below the &quot;You found a gem&quot; you will see this:\n[code:2yewrx82]\nworld&#46;registerGameObject(new GameObject(object&#46;getLocation(), 98, object&#46;getDirection(), object&#46;getType()));\n\nworld&#46;delayedSpawnObject(object&#46;getLoc(), def&#46;getRespawnTime() * 1000);\n[/code:2yewrx82]\n\nreplace with this:\n[code:2yewrx82]\nif (DataConversions&#46;random(1, 100) &lt;= def&#46;getExhausted()) {\n\nworld&#46;registerGameObject(new GameObject(object&#46;getLocation(), 98, object&#46;getDirection(), object&#46;getType()));\n\nworld&#46;delayedSpawnObject(newobject&#46;getLoc(), def&#46;getRespawnTime() * 1000);\n\n}\n[/code:2yewrx82]\n\nNow lets edit the ObjectMining.xml (located on Server/conf/server/defs/extras) adding the percent value for each mining rock. Like i did with these:\n[code:2yewrx82]\n   &lt;entry&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;176&lt;/int&gt;&lt;!-- Bluerite --&gt;\n      &lt;ObjectMiningDef&gt;\n         &lt;requiredLvl&gt;1&lt;/requiredLvl&gt;\n         &lt;oreId&gt;266&lt;/oreId&gt;\n         &lt;exp&gt;5&lt;/exp&gt;\n         &lt;respawnTime&gt;15&lt;/respawnTime&gt;\n         &lt;exhausted&gt;100&lt;/exhausted&gt;\n      &lt;/ObjectMiningDef&gt;\n   &lt;/entry&gt;\n   &lt;entry&gt;\n      &lt;int&gt;100&lt;/int&gt;&lt;!-- Copper --&gt;\n      &lt;ObjectMiningDef&gt;\n         &lt;requiredLvl&gt;1&lt;/requiredLvl&gt;\n         &lt;oreId&gt;150&lt;/oreId&gt;\n         &lt;exp&gt;18&lt;/exp&gt;\n         &lt;respawnTime&gt;3&lt;/respawnTime&gt;\n         &lt;exhausted&gt;20&lt;/exhausted&gt;\n      &lt;/ObjectMiningDef&gt;\n   &lt;/entry&gt;\n[/code:2yewrx82]\n\nFor example: a value of 100 means rock will exhaust on one successful swing but a value of 95 means 5% chance of extra ore. \n\nI tested with different values until i fell it was right, this are my exhausting values for each one:\n\nbluerite 100, clay 10, tin 20, cooper 20, iron 40, silver 50, \ncoal 55, gold 60, mith 60, addy 75, rune 95\n\nAnd finally!  ;D on ObjectMiningDef.java u need to add\n\n[code:2yewrx82]\npublic int exhausted;\n[/code:2yewrx82]\nand \n[code:2yewrx82]\n    public int getExhausted() {\n        return exhausted;\n    }\n[/code:2yewrx82]', '67fb49178fae3f20f32de8ad52128d6f', 0, 'AIA=', '2yewrx82', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(196, 175, 12, 2, 0, '108.162.237.158', 1382808671, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'MySQL replace itemdef id incremental minus 1', '[code:29uoz8fw]SELECT * FROM lupus_regnum&#46;dq_itemdef where id &gt; &quot;1221&quot; ;\ndelete from lupus_regnum&#46;dq_itemdef where id = &quot;1222&quot;;\nupdate lupus_regnum&#46;dq_itemdef set id = id - 1 where id &gt; 1222;\nSELECT * FROM lupus_regnum&#46;dq_itemdef where id &gt; &quot;1221&quot; ;[/code:29uoz8fw]\n\nThis removes the duplicate red crystal and then reduces the item ID by 1 to bring everything back in line. Fixes an item number DQ bug.', 'f3655d84c523b477ba56bfd507f8a245', 0, 'AIA=', '29uoz8fw', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0);
